## Reproducible playbook

1. `nvm use` (or `asdf install`) — pin the Node version to `.nvmrc`.
2. `npm ci` — clean install from lockfile.
3. Copy `.env.example` → `.env.local`, fill in dev credentials per the secret-management doc.
4. `npm run db:migrate` (or equivalent) — apply migrations to local DB.
5. `npm run dev` — start the dev server.
6. `npm test` — confirm baseline tests pass before changes.
7. Make the change. Add or update tests.
8. `npm run lint && npm run typecheck && npm test` — full local gate before pushing.
9. Push branch; verify the preview deploy URL renders the change.
10. Merge.

